sub_title: Competence Development Specialist Global Asset Management. Professor USACH.
summary:
I am a professional in Chile and abroad with 20 years of experience in Human Resources and Operational Excellence in multinational and national companies, leading organizational development and consulting areas.
My background had recognised from the Chilean Government in three times, for best practices in on-the-job training in mining, regional employability support and health & safety.
I have given advise to around a hundred companies to certify their processes under ISO standards as well as to more than 2.000 workers on several occupational profiles.
My strengths in cultural transformation, development and implementation of systems, definition of KPI's and focus on continuous improvement have allowed the profitability of budgets and increased performance and empowerment of the teams I have integrated and led. 
I have made great strides in the development of career systems, training centres and consultancy, with proven results. In addition, as a university professor and national and international speaker, I have shared my knowledge and experience with other professionals and students, providing a unique and valuable perspective. 
My goal is to continue to grow professionally and add value to the companies and people I work with, driving success and sustainable development in the organisations and industry.
